info.description: This is a REST API documentation for Risk Gap Targeting Service of Inovalon Inc., risk adjustment module for Medicare Advantage (CMS), commercial (HHS) or Chronic Illness and Disability Payment System (CDPS) patients based on machine learning algorithms. You can find out more about Inovalon at [https://www.inovalon.com/](https://www.inovalon.com).
info.title: RiskGapTargetingService

text/html.example:
Welcome to risk gap targeting Service !

Please POST your requests through /detect or /update with body as application/json. To try out API and view the documentation, please view /documentation.

post.summary: risk gap detection for both retrospective and prospective purpose with practitioner recommendation
post.description: Core pipeline of risk gap detection based on one patient's prior and current period of claims data and return documented conditions, gap conditions with confidence and corresponding supporting evidences with practitioner recommendations.

patch.summary: train and add a model ML into server for one model version ID

delete.summary: delete entire machine learning model of certain model_version_ID

correlation_id.description: the ID of this call for developers debugging reference.

today_date.description: the date making this API call with format "YYYY-MM-DD".

target_year.description: an integer the target service year, all prior years' data will treated as historical data and data under target_year will be treated as current service year. If not provided, model will use the server sytem today's year.

model_version_ID.description: an integer of model version ID in Inovalon database MPBWDB1.CARA2_Controller.dbo.ModelVersions; note this package only support CDPS, CMS and HHS

threshold.description: the threhold of output confidence level (only return those suspected gaps with confidence greater than threshold).

get_indicators.description: if true, return top n indicators of claim codes that contribute the most to the suspected, or return all ICD codes the directly indicating such HCCs. By defualt the parameter is true.

top_indicators.description: number of indicators to output for suspected gaps if get_indicators is true. By default the parameter is 5.

service_date.description: the service/encounter date of the corresponding claim code was documented.

code_type.description: the claim type, only accept "ICD9DX", "ICD10DX", "CPT", "HCPCS", "NDC9", "ICD9PX", "ICD10PX" or "DRG".

code.description: the code under corresponding code type with all decimal removed.

pra_id.description: the practitioner ID who reported this claim code.

spec_id.description: the Inovalon specialist ID for this practitioner.
